Nebraska Energy LLC incident investigation findings and recommendations and the resolution thereof are documented.  Nebraska Energy LLC has implemented a system to timely address and resolve all incident investigation findings and recommendations through a written schedule.  All incident investigation recommendation resolutions are communicated to all effected employees. The two most recent compliance audit reports are maintained in the PSM filing system.  

CHEMICAL-SPECIFIC PREVENTION STEPS

The processes at Nebraska Energy LLC have hazards that must be managed for continued safe 
operation.  The following is a description of existing safety features applicable to prevention of 
accidental releases of regulated substances at Nebraska Energy LLC.

Universal Prevention Activities

The accident prevention program summarized previously is applied to all RMP-covered processes at Nebraska Energy LLC.  Collectively, these prevention program activities help prevent potential accident scenarios that could be caused by equipment failures and human errors.

Specialized Safety Features

Nebraska Energy LLC has safety features on the RMP covered process to (1) contain/control a release, (2) detect a release, and (3) reduce the consequences of (mitigate) a release.  The following types of safety features are used in the covered processes:

? Release Containment / Control;
? Valves to permit isolation of the process (manual or automated);
? Maximum intended inventory of regulated substances;
? Automated shutdown systems for specific process parameters (e.g., high level);
? Curbing or diking to contain liquid releases;
? Atmospheric relief and vent devices;
? Release Mitigation;
? Fire extinguishers;
? Trained emergency response personnel; and
? Personal protective equipment 

